    <h1> How to Stay Safe Online </h1>
<p> Now that we know about the common cyber threats, it is time to learn how to defend against them. 
    Protecting yourself online doesn't require you to be a tech expert. By following a few simple and effective practices, 
    you can significantly reduce the risk of your personal information falling into the wrong hands. </p>

<img src="Images/3d-lock-password-free-png.png" width="220" />

<h2> How to Create Strong Passwords </h2>
<p> Your password is your first line of defense. A strong password should be long (at least 12 characters) and include a mix of uppercase letters, lowercase letters, numbers, and symbols. 
    Avoid using easily guessable information like your name, birthdate, or "123456". For maximum security, use a different password for every account and consider using a Password Manager to keep track of them all. </p>

<h2> Safe Browsing Habits </h2>
<p> Not every website is safe. Always look for the padlock icon in the address bar and make sure the website's URL starts with "https://" instead of just "http://". 
    Be cautious when clicking on pop-up ads, opening suspicious emails, or downloading files from unknown sources. Remember: if an offer looks too good to be true, it is probably a scam! </p>

    <img src="Images/6071531.png" width="250" />
<h2> Basic Ways to Protect Your Data </h2>
<ol> 
    <li> Enable Two-Factor Authentication (2FA) – Adds an extra layer of security by requiring a code from your phone in addition to your password. </li>
    <li> Keep Software Updated – Always update your operating system, browser, and apps to patch known security holes. </li> 
    <li> Backup Your Files – Keep copies of your important data on an external hard drive or a secure cloud service to protect against ransomware. </li>
</ol>



<h3> Check Your Security! </h3>
<p> Want to see if your email or phone number has ever been compromised in a public data breach? 
    A well-known and safe tool created by security experts to check this is <a href="https://haveibeenpwned.com/" target="_blank"> Have I Been Pwned </a>. 
    It is a great place to start taking control of your digital footprint.</p>
